# Architecture Gate — STRICT Pre-Edit Blocker

> Master: `restaurant-voice-agent.mdc`. **Do not edit any file in this glob until gate passes.**

## STOP — Complete before first line of code

### 1. Mandatory reads (all required)

- [ ] `restaurant-voice-agent.mdc` — full RULE COMPLIANCE CHECK block prepared
- [ ] `ARCHITECTURE_GATE.md`
- [ ] `agent-vault/lessons.md`
- [ ] `git log --oneline -5` — know what shipped recently

### 2. Runtime confirmation (state in compliance block)

- [ ] Production = `v4_pipeline_clean.py` → `ConversationFSM` — NOT legacy, NOT training path
- [ ] Category B = `_phase_committed()` only
- [ ] `check_forced_commits()` = training ONLY — do not modify for production fixes

### 3. Absolute prohibitions — any YES = do not edit

- [ ] Adding keyword/regex for intent (including `_FAQ_KW`, `_PRICE_KW`, denial lists for routing)
- [ ] Adding `[TOOL:...]` text extraction
- [ ] Adding tenant string literals in brain
- [ ] New state field without `to_dict()`/`from_dict()`
- [ ] LLM prompt that can emit Category B tools
- [ ] Changing validation to mask product bug
- [ ] ORing `order_commit_state.confirmed` into `slots.confirmed` — FSM track only (KI-025)
- [ ] Truthy-check writes in `_slots_to_state` (`if slots.X:` instead of `if slots.X is not None:`) — stale data persists (KI-026)
- [ ] `_force_commit_tools_if_missing` without `next_state == COMMITTED` gate — premature fires (KI-027)
- [ ] FSM `step()` returning non-empty `response_text` for any intent in `_GROUNDING_REQUIRED_INTENTS` — must set `grounding_required=True` + clear `response_text` (KI-029)

### 4. Only allowed exception to keyword ban

- `_TRIVIAL_TURN_RE` — empty/noise turn bypass ONLY. Nothing else.

### 5. Post-edit requirements (before saying "done")

- [ ] `pytest server/tests/test_conversation_fsm.py` → 65/65
- [ ] Server restarted, `lstart` verified
- [ ] `--smoke` run with X/Y reported
- [ ] Pass rate did not decrease (if it did → revert or fix, do not proceed)

## Redis

Every `ConversationState` field in `to_dict()` AND `from_dict()`. No exceptions.
